cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about image-to-image translation using unsupervised learning, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a novel dual-GAN mechanism, which involves training two GANs simultaneously, and this approach is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve multiple image translation tasks, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the performance gain of DualGAN over a single GAN, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE).
